    "comment": "Rationale: Characterisation of AMPA receptor subunits from outside-out patches from transfected HEK cells.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has ligand-gated ion channel receptor activity and is localized in the presynaptic membrane (shown with high-resolution technique). The inference to term ligand-gated ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential (GO:0099507) is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[P19493] SyNGO ID 1204 (PMID:15610164, EM). Experimental description: Human AMPA receptor cDNA was cloned from a human hippocampus cDNAbank(Stratagene,Amsterdam,TheNetherlands).Subunit cDNA was produced by PCR mutagenesis. The constructs were each subcloned into pcDNA3 expression vectors for transfection (Invitro- gen, Groningen, The Netherlands). Transformed human embryonic kidney (HEK) 293 cells were cultured in Dulbecco's Modified Eagle's medium (DMEM), supplemented with 10% fetal calf serum, 100 U/ mL penicillin and 100 mg/mL streptomycin at 37 8C in a 5% CO2 : 95% air incubator.",
